OL,3,CCouncil plans right to roam
OL,4,Crestrictions at Center Parcs site
OL,6,FScottish Borders Council has agreed to
OL,7,Fcontinue with plans to introduce a
OL,8,Fbyelaw restricting the right to roam
OL,9,Fon the proposed site of Scotland's
OL,10,Ffirst Center Parcs.
OL,12,FThe byelaw would restrict public
OL,13,Faccess rights over land at Huntlaw and
OL,14,FMuirfield Farm, near Hawick, but it
OL,15,Fwill need ministerial approval from
OL,16,Fthe Scottish Government to go ahead.
OL,18,FCouncillors had already agreed
OL,19,Funanimously to create the byelaw and
OL,20,Fconduct a statutory consultation
OL,21,Fprocess, which has now concluded.
