OL,4,Crestrictions at Center Parcs site
OL,6,F"We recognise the concerns raised by
OL,7,Faccess groups and local residents but
OL,8,Fconcluded these could be mitigated by
OL,9,FCenter Parcs proposals that will bring
OL,10,Fsignificant economic and employment
OL,11,Fopportunities to the Borders."
OL,13,FThe right to roam is enshrined in
OL,14,FScottish law, under the Land Reform
OL,15,F(Scotland) Act 2003. It mandates that
OL,16,Fthe public can 'responsibly' access
OL,17,Fmost of the land and inland water in
OL,18,FScotland for recreational and
OL,19,Feducational purposes.
