OL,6,FThe Scottish Rights of Way and Access
OL,7,FSociety expressed its opposition to
OL,8,Fthe plans earlier this month, citing
OL,9,F"strong concerns about the wider
OL,10,Fimplications of the byelaws for
OL,11,Fsimilar caravan and holiday parks,"
OL,12,Fwho might "cite (this byelaw) as a
OL,13,Fprecedent" and thus "erode access
OL,14,Frights nationally".
